00:30:25.890 --> 00:30:27.091
Why would you do that?

00:30:27.091 --> 00:30:29.060
First, forgetting your password sucks

00:30:29.060 --> 00:30:31.563
and getting locked out of your PC sucks more.

00:30:31.563 --> 00:30:34.432
Second, it can actually be more secure

00:30:34.432 --> 00:30:36.935
because typing out your password means a key logger

00:30:36.935 --> 00:30:39.370
or a particularly nosy housemate

00:30:39.370 --> 00:30:41.306
might be able to read your keystrokes.

00:30:41.306 --> 00:30:43.074
This way, Windows Hello makes it

00:30:43.074 --> 00:30:44.676
so someone gaining access to your PC

00:30:44.676 --> 00:30:47.779
doesn't also gain access to your Microsoft account.

00:30:47.779 --> 00:30:49.714
To secure your PC even better

00:30:49.714 --> 00:30:51.783
than a password alone ever could,

00:30:51.783 --> 00:30:53.451
